HEADWORD: Chemiotaxis
<hw>Chem`i*o*tax"is</hw>}</mhw>. <ety>[<ets>Chem</ets>ical + Gr. <?/
arrangement, fr. <?/ to arrange.]</ety> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>The
sensitiveness exhibited by small free-swimming organisms, as bacteria,
zoospores of alg⟦ae⟧, etc., to chemical substances held in solution.
They may be attracted (<stype>positive chemotaxis</stype>) or repelled
(<stype>negative chemotaxis</stype>).</def> --
<wordforms><wf>Chem`o*tac"tic</wf> <pr>(#)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> --
<wf>Chem`o*tac"tic*al*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
